		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />you could use the command prompt(cmd.exe) and use &quot;fc&quot; it compares 2 files byte by byte. Just to see if your files are corrupted.<br /><br />Try this command on one of your copied files. This assumes your file is named &quot;file1.avi&quot; and is on c:\ and your external drive letter is e:\. <br />&quot;fc /b c:\file1.avi e:\file1.avi&quot;

		

